    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-15T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="363"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3839: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norem</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kaunas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 15, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Russian armored divisions crossed the Lithuanian border at several points at
                    2 p.m. today following Moscow rejection of Rastikis’ appointment. Demands said
                    to include a favorable government with possible Communist inclusion, the trial
                    of former Lithuanian Minister of the Interior and of the Director of Security,
                    increased garrisons and free movement of troops. The Lithuanian Government
                    accepted and Soviet Minister and Assistant Soviet Commissar <pb facs="0381"
                        n="369" xml:id="pg_369"/> for Foreign Affairs<note n="28" xml:id="d363fn28"
                        >Vladimir Georgevich Dekanozov.</note> left Moscow by plane at noon.
                    Lithuanian Government awaits their arrival before making further proposals.
                    Attitude here of officials one of great tension and apprehension.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norem</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
